Status reason
-------------
Bit-exact resume verification was the gate before pilot grid. Now
passed. The bpb divergence at step 100 between Smoke B (1.534) and
Smoke C (1.493) is explained by the LR-warmdown schedule being a
function of num_iterations: Smoke B's schedule decays to step 100,
Smoke C's decays to step 150, so the same step has different LR mults.
Verified by checking lrm column in the log.

